    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="772"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6124/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-12T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1921—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Department of Labor has just informed State Department that arrangements were
                    made by one of its representatives with the Latvian representative in New York
                    for transit through Latvia of twenty-four aliens who sailed from New York
                    December 23, 1920, via S.S. <hi rend="italic">Imperator</hi>, and that these
                    deportees were transshipped to Libau, <pb facs="0899" n="803" xml:id="pg_803"/>
                    where they were met by representatives of Latvia, placed aboard a train and
                    taken to Riga, and turned over to Soviet representatives.</p>
                <p>If any complications arose, cable facts briefly; otherwise submit full report by
                    mail.</p>
                <p>Do you perceive any objection to future similar informal arrangements by Labor
                    Department?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
